21/10/2003
ANKARA, Turkey -- Local television channel TRT 2 reported Monday (20 October) that Turkey would need Vatican approval of its EU membership bid.
Unnamed European Commission sources told the station that convincing the Vatican of the benefits from accepting Turkey in the EU would be crucial in securing the support of European public opinion.
The sources say every step Turkey takes towards securing religious freedoms would be watched by the Vatican.
(TRT 2, Anadolu Agency - 20/10/03)
